    "Therefore, our reproduced baseline results (\"W/O\") reported in Table 2 are closely aligned with those in Table 1 of TabWak.The discrepancies between our \"W/O\" results and those reported in the original TabSyn paper [40] stem from the two modifications mentioned above.",
    "As reported in the TabSyn paper itself, the original score-based TabSyn model outperformed the TabSyn-DDPM variant in generation quality owing to its tailored diffusion process in continuous latent space.",
    "Additionally, the deterministic nature of the DDIM sampler may reduce data diversity compared to the original score-based SDE sampler.",
    "Nevertheless, the DDIM sampler is essential for TabWak, as its watermark detection relies on the inversion process.In Table 10, we also present the evaluation results of our methods on synthetic tabular data generated by original TabSyn implementation.",
